name: Catholic Charities of San Francisco
orgDescription: Founded in 1907 and rooted in our faith traditions of charity and justice, Catholic Charities supports families, aging and disabled adults, and youth through social services and opportunities for healthy growth and development.

name: Order of Malta, The Western Association
orgDescription: The Order of St John of Jerusalem is one of the oldest institutions of Western and Christian civilization.  Present in Palestine in around 1050, it is a lay religious Order, traditionally of military, chivalrous, and noble nature.  Its 12,500 members include Professed Friars and others who have made vows of obedience.  The other Knights and Dames are lay members, devoted to the exercise of Christian virtue and charity.  What distinguishes the Knights and Dames of Malta is their commitment to reaching their spiritual perfection within the Church and to expending their energies serving the poor and the sick.

name: Radio Maria
orgDescription: Radio Maria serves the Catholic Church as a network committed to calling for conversion through programming which offers prayer, catechism and human development.

name: Catholic Relief Services
orgDescription: Catholic Relief Services is the official international humanitarian agency of the Catholic community in the United States. We ease suffering and provide assistance to people in need in 93 countries, without regard to race, religion or nationality.

name: Relevant Radio
orgDescription: Now in its 14th year, Relevant Radio® is “Talk Radio for Catholic Life”, broadcasting 24/7 on 33 stations and produces 70 hrs of weekly original programming.

name: Women's Care Center Foundation
orgDescription: The nation's largest pregnancy resource center, Women's Care Center serves 25,000 women annually from 22 locations in 7 states.  This unique unconditionally loving Catholic model is a magnet for pregnant women in need. Donors like you sustain the center as a beacon of hope for abortion vulnerable women. Because of the support and love, over 97% of those who receive counseling and an ultrasound choose life for their babies.  The center also offers education, classes and counseling so that women become better parents and create more nurturing and self-sufficient families.
